"title": "6730: reinstatement",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6730",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Restoration to a previous state or position. It is demonstrated in human relationships and also by God in his love and grace restoring fallen humanity and lifting up his people to their former place within his service.</p>\n<h2>The basis of reinstatement</h2>\n<h3>God does not remember sin</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:12\">PSA 103:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:17\">ISA 38:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:25\">ISA 43:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:44\">EZK 20:44</a></p>\n<h3>God's unfailing love</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:28\">PSA 89:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:22\">LAM 3:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:8\">HOS 11:8</a></p>\n<h2>God's reinstatement of fallen humanity</h2>\n<h3>Humanity's unique calling</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:6-Heb2:8\">HEB 2:6–2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:4-Ps8:6\">PSA 8:4–8:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26-Gen1:27\">GEN 1:26–1:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:7\">ISA 43:7</a></p>\n<h3>Humanity's fall and reinstatement</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:23-Rom3:24\">ROM 3:23–3:24</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:14\">2TH 2:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:15-Rom5:19\">ROM 5:15–5:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:17\">ROM 8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:12\">EPH 1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:10\">HEB 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:1\">1PE 5:1</a></p>\n<h2>God's reinstatement of Israel</h2>\n<h3>The promise of reinstatement</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:8\">MIC 4:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:26\">ISA 1:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:10\">ISA 60:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:9\">HAG 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech1:17\">ZEC 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech10:6-Zech10:8\">ZEC 10:6–10:8</a></p>\n<h3>Reinstatement as God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:23\">HOS 2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:25\">ROM 9:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:10\">1PE 2:10</a></p>\n<h3>Reinstatement as God's bride</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:5-Isa54:8\">ISA 54:5–54:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:12-Jer3:14\">JER 3:12–3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:14-Hos2:20\">HOS 2:14–2:20</a></p>\n<h3>Reinstatement in the land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:10-Jer33:16\">JER 33:10–33:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:9\">2CH 30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:16-Jer31:17\">JER 31:16–31:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:10-Hos11:11\">HOS 11:10–11:11</a></p>\n<h2>God's reinstatement of his servants</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:22\">JDG 16:22</a> <em>Samson's hair begins to grow again, indicating his renewed call to serve God</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:19\">JER 15:19</a> <em>God will continue to speak through a repentant Jeremiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:34-Dan4:36\">DAN 4:34–4:36</a> <em>Nebuchadnezzar's sanity and kingdom is restored</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:1-Jonah3:2\">JON 3:1–3:2</a> <em>God renews Jonah's commission</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:15-John21:17\">JHN 21:15–21:17</a> <em>Jesus Christ reinstates Peter after his denial.</em></p>\n<h2>Further examples of reinstatement</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:13\">GEN 40:13</a> <em>Pharaoh's cupbearer reinstated</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:6-1Sam19:7\">1SA 19:6–19:7</a> <em>David reinstated by Saul</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam9:7\">2SA 9:7</a> <em>Mephibosheth reinstated by David</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:33\">2SA 14:33</a> <em>Absalom reinstated by David</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:30\">DAN 3:30</a> <em>Nebuchadnezzar reinstates Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos3:2-Hos3:3\">HOS 3:2–3:3</a> <em>Gomer reinstated as Hosea's wife</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:22-Luke15:24\">LUK 15:22–15:24</a> <em>the prodigal reinstated by his father</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:10\">PHM 1:10</a> <em>Paul asks Philemon to reinstate his slave Onesimus</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:24\">PHM 1:24</a> <em>John Mark, formerly rejected, has here been reinstated as Paul's companion.</em></p>",
